Subject: [PATCH] Add Resources page, include YEMZI, and fix modal deep-linking
 with nav improvements
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

### Motivation
- Surface a small, curated set of external tall-focused resources from a dedicated `/resources/` page to improve discoverability.
- Fix a feedback/submit modal deep-link bug so `?modal=feedback` and `?modal=submit` open correctly on load.
- Add a recent submission (`YEMZI`) to the women’s directory dataset so new reports appear in the source data.
- Improve navigation so the new Resources page is reachable from both shared static pages and the SPA footer.

### Description
- Added a new static page at `resources/index.html` with metadata, a featured link to `https://talltour.com/`, and a CTA to suggest more resources via the feedback modal.
- Centralized URL parsing in `readURLState()` and returned a `modal` field, and updated app initialization in `assets/app.js` to use `st.modal` for opening `submit`/`feedback` modals on load.
- Inserted `Resources` into the shared static-page header (`assets/shared.js`) and normalized the SPA footer entry for `Tall Resources` in `assets/app.js` to match other trust links.
- Added the `YEMZI` record to `data/women.json` and added `/resources/` to `sitemap.xml`.

### Testing
- Verified presence and rendering strings with ripgrep and file inspections using `rg` and `nl` for `resources/`, `Tall Resources`, and `modal` references; these checks succeeded.
- Confirmed `data/women.json` contains the new `YEMZI` entry via `rg` and inspected the surrounding JSON slice; this check succeeded.
- Confirmed `readURLState()` returns `modal` and that `initApp()` uses `st.modal` instead of re-parsing `location.search` by scanning `assets/app.js`; this check succeeded.
- Ran repository status and commit checks (`git status`, `git log`) to validate working tree consistency after edits; these checks succeeded.
